{"word":"H3244 - יַנְשׁוּף - yanshûwph - yan-shoof' - Owl","slug":"H3244","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">יַנְשׁוּף</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>yanshûwph"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yan-shoof'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Owl"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D9;&#x05E0;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D5;&#x05E3;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D9;&#x05E0;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05E3; - yanshu&#x0302;ph  yansho&#x0302;ph</b> - <i>yan-shoof', yan-shofe'</i><p/>Apparently from <a href=\"#/H4398\">H4398</a>; an unclean (aquatic) bird; probably the <i>heron</i> (perhaps from its <i>blowing</i> cry, or because the <i>night heron</i> is meant (compare <a href=\"#/H5399\">H5399</a>)): - (great) owl."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5398\">H5398</a>, <a href=\"#/H5399\">H5399</a>"}]}